python
import tarfile
import os
import subprocess

# Extract the uploaded file
extract_path = '/mnt/data/node_extracted'
tar_file_path = '/mnt/data/node-v20.6.0-linux-x64.tar.xz'

# Create the directory for extraction if it doesn't exist
if not os.path.exists(extract_path):
    os.makedirs(extract_path)

# Extract the tar.xz file
with tarfile.open(tar_file_path, 'r:xz') as tar:
    tar.extractall(path=extract_path)

# Check if bin/node file exists
node_bin_path = os.path.join(extract_path, 'node-v20.6.0-linux-x64', 'bin', 'node')

node_bin_exists = os.path.exists(node_bin_path)

# Run "bin/node -v" with subprocess if bin/node exists
node_version_output = None
if node_bin_exists:
    try:
        node_version_output = subprocess.run([node_bin_path, '-v'], capture_output=True, text=True).stdout.strip()
    except Exception as e:
        node_version_output = str(e)

# JavaScript code to create a mosaic effect on the image using the jimp module
js_code = """
const Jimp = require('jimp');

class Mosaicifier {
    constructor(filePath) {
        this.filePath = filePath;
        this.image = null;
    }

    async convert(options) {
        this.image = await Jimp.read(this.filePath);
        // Assuming some conversion here based on the options
        // (the exact conversion is not provided in the original code snippet)
        return this;
    }

    async turnGrayscale() {
        this.image.grayscale();
        return this;
    }

    get mosaicCount() {
        // Assuming this property should return some count related to the mosaic
        // (the exact logic is not provided in the original code snippet)
        return 1; // Placeholder value
    }

    async save(options) {
        await this.image.writeAsync(options.destination);
        return this;
    }

    async saveAsBlob(options) {
        // Convert image to buffer and return it
        const buffer = await this.image.getBufferAsync(options.type);
        return buffer;
    }
}

(async () => {
    let filePath = './HEE06985 copy.jpg';
    const mosaicifier = new Mosaicifier(filePath);
    try {
        const width = 10;
        const height = 10;
        const borderColor = '#FFFFFF';
        const borderSize = 2;
        
        const convertedInstance = await mosaicifier.convert({
            tile: { width, height, borderColor, borderSize },
        });
        await convertedInstance.turnGrayscale();
        const count = convertedInstance.mosaicCount;
        await convertedInstance.save({
            destination: './converted_image_mosaic.jpg',
            type: 'image/jpeg'
        });
        const imageBlob = await convertedInstance.saveAsBlob({ type: 'image/jpeg' });
    } catch (error) {
        console.error(error);
    }
})();
"""

# Updated JavaScript code with basic mosaic effect implementation
js_code_mosaic = """
const Jimp = require('jimp');

class Mosaicifier {
    constructor(filePath) {
        this.filePath = filePath;
        this.image = null;
    }

    async convert(options) {
        this.image = await Jimp.read(this.filePath);
        
        const { width, height } = options.tile;
        for (let x = 0; x < this.image.bitmap.width; x += width) {
            for (let y = 0; y < this.image.bitmap.height; y += height) {
                const cropped = this.image.clone().crop(x, y, width, height);
                const avgColor = cropped.clone().resize(1, 1).getPixelColor(0, 0);
                this.image.scan(x, y, width, height, (x, y, idx) => {
                    this.image.setPixelColor(avgColor, x, y);
                });
            }
        }
        
        return this;
    }

    async turnGrayscale() {
        this.image.grayscale();
        return this;
    }

    get mosaicCount() {
        // Assuming this property should return some count related to the mosaic
        // (the exact logic is not provided in the original code snippet)
        return 1; // Placeholder value
    }

    async save(options) {
        await this.image.writeAsync(options.destination);
        return this;
    }

    async saveAsBlob(options) {
        // Convert image to buffer and return it
        const buffer = await this.image.getBufferAsync(options.type);
        return buffer;
    }
}

(async () => {
    let filePath = './HEE06985 copy.jpg';
    const mosaicifier = new Mosaicifier(filePath);
    try {
        const width = 50; // Adjust tile width
        const height = 50; // Adjust tile height
        const borderColor = '#FFFFFF';
        const borderSize = 2;
        
        const convertedInstance = await mosaicifier.convert({
            tile: { width, height, borderColor, borderSize },
        });
        await convertedInstance.turnGrayscale();
        const count = convertedInstance.mosaicCount;
        await convertedInstance.save({
            destination: './converted_image_mosaic.jpg',
            type: 'image/jpeg'
        });
        const imageBlob = await convertedInstance.saveAsBlob({ type: 'image/jpeg' });
    } catch (error) {
        console.error(error);
    }
})();
"""

# Save the updated JavaScript code to index.js

python
# Updated JavaScript code with improved mosaic effect implementation
js_code_mosaic_improved = """
const Jimp = require('jimp');

class Mosaicifier {
    constructor(filePath) {
        this.filePath = filePath;
        this.image = null;
    }

    async convert(options) {
        this.image = await Jimp.read(this.filePath);
        
        const { width, height } = options.tile;
        for (let x = 0; x < this.image.bitmap.width; x += width) {
            for (let y = 0; y < this.image.bitmap.height; y += height) {
                let avgColor = { r: 0, g: 0, b: 0, a: 0 };
                let pixelCount = 0;
                
                this.image.scan(x, y, width, height, (px, py, idx) => {
                    avgColor.r += this.image.bitmap.data[idx + 0];
                    avgColor.g += this.image.bitmap.data[idx + 1];
                    avgColor.b += this.image.bitmap.data[idx + 2];
                    avgColor.a += this.image.bitmap.data[idx + 3];
                    pixelCount++;
                });
                
                avgColor.r = Math.round(avgColor.r / pixelCount);
                avgColor.g = Math.round(avgColor.g / pixelCount);
                avgColor.b = Math.round(avgColor.b / pixelCount);
                avgColor.a = Math.round(avgColor.a / pixelCount);
                
                const hexColor = Jimp.rgbaToInt(avgColor.r, avgColor.g, avgColor.b, avgColor.a);
                
                this.image.scan(x, y, width, height, (px, py, idx) => {
                    this.image.setPixelColor(hexColor, px, py);
                });
            }
        }
        
        return this;
    }

    async turnGrayscale() {
        this.image.grayscale();
        return this;
    }

    get mosaicCount() {
        // Placeholder value
        return 1;
    }

    async save(options) {
        await this.image.writeAsync(options.destination);
        return this;
    }

    async saveAsBlob(options) {
        const buffer = await this.image.getBufferAsync(options.type);
        return buffer;
    }
}

(async () => {
    let filePath = './HEE06985 copy.jpg';
    const mosaicifier = new Mosaicifier(filePath);
    try {
        const width = 50;
        const height = 50;
        const borderColor = '#FFFFFF';
        const borderSize = 2;
        
        const convertedInstance = await mosaicifier.convert({
            tile: { width, height, borderColor, borderSize },
        });
        await convertedInstance.turnGrayscale();
        const count = convertedInstance.mosaicCount;
        await convertedInstance.save({
            destination: './converted_image_mosaic.jpg',
            type: 'image/jpeg'
        });
        const imageBlob = await convertedInstance.saveAsBlob({ type: 'image/jpeg' });
    } catch (error) {
        console.error(error);
    }
})();
"""

# Save the improved JavaScript code to index.js
with open(index_js_path, 'w') as f:
    f.write(js_code_mosaic_improved)

# Running the improved JavaScript code using Node.js
try:
    output = subprocess.run([node_bin_path, index_js_path], cwd=node_project_path, capture_output=True, text=True)
    js_output_improved = output.stdout.strip()
except Exception as e:
    js_output_improved = str(e)

# Updated JavaScript code with improved mosaic effect implementation and mosaicCount feature
js_code_mosaic_count = """
const Jimp = require('jimp');

class Mosaicifier {
    constructor(filePath) {
        this.filePath = filePath;
        this.image = null;
        this.tileWidth = 0;
        this.tileHeight = 0;
    }

    async convert(options) {
        this.image = await Jimp.read(this.filePath);
        
        const { width, height } = options.tile;
        this.tileWidth = width;
        this.tileHeight = height;
        
        for (let x = 0; x < this.image.bitmap.width; x += width) {
            for (let y = 0; y < this.image.bitmap.height; y += height) {
                let avgColor = { r: 0, g: 0, b: 0, a: 0 };
                let pixelCount = 0;
                
                this.image.scan(x, y, width, height, (px, py, idx) => {
                    avgColor.r += this.image.bitmap.data[idx + 0];
                    avgColor.g += this.image.bitmap.data[idx + 1];
                    avgColor.b += this.image.bitmap.data[idx + 2];
                    avgColor.a += this.image.bitmap.data[idx + 3];
                    pixelCount++;
                });
                
                avgColor.r = Math.round(avgColor.r / pixelCount);
                avgColor.g = Math.round(avgColor.g / pixelCount);
                avgColor.b = Math.round(avgColor.b / pixelCount);
                avgColor.a = Math.round(avgColor.a / pixelCount);
                
                const hexColor = Jimp.rgbaToInt(avgColor.r, avgColor.g, avgColor.b, avgColor.a);
                
                this.image.scan(x, y, width, height, (px, py, idx) => {
                    this.image.setPixelColor(hexColor, px, py);
                });
            }
        }
        
        return this;
    }

    async turnGrayscale() {
        this.image.grayscale();
        return this;
    }

    get mosaicCount() {
        const xTiles = Math.ceil(this.image.bitmap.width / this.tileWidth);
        const yTiles = Math.ceil(this.image.bitmap.height / this.tileHeight);
        return xTiles * yTiles;
    }

    async save(options) {
        await this.image.writeAsync(options.destination);
        return this;
    }

    async saveAsBlob(options) {
        const buffer = await this.image.getBufferAsync(options.type);
        return buffer;
    }
}

(async () => {
    let filePath = './HEE06985 copy.jpg';
    const mosaicifier = new Mosaicifier(filePath);
    try {
        const width = 50;
        const height = 50;
        const borderColor = '#FFFFFF';
        const borderSize = 2;
        
        const convertedInstance = await mosaicifier.convert({
            tile: { width, height, borderColor, borderSize },
        });
        await convertedInstance.turnGrayscale();
        const count = convertedInstance.mosaicCount;
        console.log('Total mosaic tiles:', count);

        });
        const imageBlob = await convertedInstance.saveAsBlob({ type: 'image/jpeg' });

        console.error(error);
    }
})();
"""

  • 각 타일의 외곽 픽셀을 borderColor로 설정합니다.
  • borderSize를 사용하여 테두리의 두께를 조절합니다.

# Updated JavaScript code with border application
js_code_mosaic_border = """
const Jimp = require('jimp');

class Mosaicifier {
    constructor(filePath) {
        this.filePath = filePath;
        this.image = null;
        this.tileWidth = 0;
        this.tileHeight = 0;
    }

    async convert(options) {
        this.image = await Jimp.read(this.filePath);
        
        const { width, height, borderColor, borderSize } = options.tile;
        this.tileWidth = width;
        this.tileHeight = height;
        
        for (let x = 0; x < this.image.bitmap.width; x += width) {
            for (let y = 0; y < this.image.bitmap.height; y += height) {
                let avgColor = { r: 0, g: 0, b: 0, a: 0 };
                let pixelCount = 0;
                
                this.image.scan(x, y, width, height, (px, py, idx) => {
                    avgColor.r += this.image.bitmap.data[idx + 0];
                    avgColor.g += this.image.bitmap.data[idx + 1];
                    avgColor.b += this.image.bitmap.data[idx + 2];
                    avgColor.a += this.image.bitmap.data[idx + 3];
                    pixelCount++;
                });
                
                avgColor.r = Math.round(avgColor.r / pixelCount);
                avgColor.g = Math.round(avgColor.g / pixelCount);
                avgColor.b = Math.round(avgColor.b / pixelCount);
                avgColor.a = Math.round(avgColor.a / pixelCount);
                
                const hexColor = Jimp.rgbaToInt(avgColor.r, avgColor.g, avgColor.b, avgColor.a);
                const borderHexColor = Jimp.cssColorToHex(borderColor);
                
                this.image.scan(x, y, width, height, (px, py, idx) => {
                    // Apply border based on the borderSize
                    if (px < x + borderSize || px >= x + width - borderSize || 
                        py < y + borderSize || py >= y + height - borderSize) {
                        this.image.setPixelColor(borderHexColor, px, py);
                    } else {
                        this.image.setPixelColor(hexColor, px, py);
                    }
                });
            }
        }
        
        return this;
    }

    async turnGrayscale() {
        this.image.grayscale();
        return this;
    }

    get mosaicCount() {
        const xTiles = Math.ceil(this.image.bitmap.width / this.tileWidth);
        const yTiles = Math.ceil(this.image.bitmap.height / this.tileHeight);
        return xTiles * yTiles;
    }

    async save(options) {
        await this.image.writeAsync(options.destination);
        return this;
    }

    async saveAsBlob(options) {
        const buffer = await this.image.getBufferAsync(options.type);
        return buffer;
    }
}

(async () => {
    let filePath = './HEE06985 copy.jpg';
    const mosaicifier = new Mosaicifier(filePath);
    try {
        const width = 50;
        const height = 50;

})();

javascript
const Jimp = require('jimp');

class Mosaicifier {
    constructor(filePath) {
        this.filePath = filePath;
        this.image = null;
        this.tileWidth = 0;
        this.tileHeight = 0;
    }

    async convert(options) {
        this.image = await Jimp.read(this.filePath);
        
        const { width, height, borderColor, borderSize } = options.tile;
        this.tileWidth = width;
        this.tileHeight = height;
        
        for (let x = 0; x < this.image.bitmap.width; x += width) {
            for (let y = 0; y < this.image.bitmap.height; y += height) {
                let avgColor = { r: 0, g: 0, b: 0, a: 0 };
                let pixelCount = 0;
                
                this.image.scan(x, y, width, height, (px, py, idx) => {
                    avgColor.r += this.image.bitmap.data[idx + 0];
                    avgColor.g += this.image.bitmap.data[idx + 1];
                    avgColor.b += this.image.bitmap.data[idx + 2];
                    avgColor.a += this.image.bitmap.data[idx + 3];
                    pixelCount++;
                });
                
                avgColor.r = Math.round(avgColor.r / pixelCount);
                avgColor.g = Math.round(avgColor.g / pixelCount);
                avgColor.b = Math.round(avgColor.b / pixelCount);
                avgColor.a = Math.round(avgColor.a / pixelCount);
                
                const hexColor = Jimp.rgbaToInt(avgColor.r, avgColor.g, avgColor.b, avgColor.a);
                const borderHexColor = Jimp.cssColorToHex(borderColor);
                
                this.image.scan(x, y, width, height, (px, py, idx) => {
                    // Apply border based on the borderSize
                    if (px < x + borderSize || px >= x + width - borderSize || 
                        py < y + borderSize || py >= y + height - borderSize) {
                        this.image.setPixelColor(borderHexColor, px, py);
                    } else {
                        this.image.setPixelColor(hexColor, px, py);
                    }
                });
            }
        }
        
        return this;
    }

    async turnGrayscale() {
        this.image.grayscale();
        return this;
    }

    get mosaicCount() {
        const xTiles = Math.ceil(this.image.bitmap.width / this.tileWidth);
        const yTiles = Math.ceil(this.image.bitmap.height / this.tileHeight);
        return xTiles * yTiles;
    }

    async save(options) {
        await this.image.writeAsync(options.destination);
        return this;
    }

    async saveAsBlob(options) {
        const buffer = await this.image.getBufferAsync(options.type);
        return buffer;
    }
}

(async () => {
    let filePath = './HEE06985 copy.jpg';
    const mosaicifier = new Mosaicifier(filePath);
    try {
        const width = 50;
        const height = 50;
        const borderColor = '#FFFFFF';
        const borderSize = 2;
        
        const convertedInstance = await mosaicifier.convert({
            tile: { width, height, borderColor, borderSize },
        });
        await convertedInstance.turnGrayscale();
        const count = convertedInstance.mosaicCount;
        console.log('Total mosaic tiles:', count);
        await convertedInstance.save({
            destination: './converted_image_mosaic.jpg',
            type: 'image/jpeg'
        });
        const imageBlob = await convertedInstance.saveAsBlob({ type: 'image/jpeg' });
    } catch (error) {
        console.error(error);
    }
})();

이 코드는 Jimp 라이브러리를 사용하여 이미지를 모자이크 처리하고, 추가적으로 그레이스케일로 변환합니다. 또한, 타일의 경계에 대해 사용자가 정의한 색상과 크기의 테두리를 적용합니다.

더 궁금하신 점이 있거나 도움이 필요하시면 알려주세요!
